Trim the @carrot{1}(trimmed) then quarter lengthways (no need to peel). Chop
widthways into small pieces. Trim the @aubergine{1} then slice into rounds
approximately 1cm thick.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #frying pan{} on medium heat. Add the carrot
and cook until soft, ~{6%minutes}. Stir in the @lamb mince{200%g} and
@ground cinnamon{1%tsp}. Cook for ~{5-6%minutes}, until the lamb has browned
(drain away any excess fat) and add the @finely chopped tomatoes with onion and
garlic{1}(finely chopped), @chicken stock powder{1} and season with a pinch of
@salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Simmer until thick and tomatoey,
~{15-20%minutes}. Stir occasionally. Preheat your #grill{} to high.

Meanwhile, arrange the aubergine slices in a single layer on a #baking tray{}
with a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} and season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.
Grill for ~{8-9%minutes} on each side. Remove from the grill and leave to the
side (leave the grill on).

> Tip: The aubergine slices should be browned and soft. If they aren't, grill
> them for a little longer. If they are getting brown too quickly, turn the
> heat down a little.

When the lamb mixture is nice and thick, pour into an #ovenproof dish{}. Lay the
aubergine on top and spoon over the @crème fraîche{150%g}. Spread the crème
fraîche with the back of a #spoon{} and sprinkle over the
@grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g}.

Grill the moussaka until the top is bubbling and brown, about ~{3-4%minutes}.

Once brown, remove the moussaka from under the grill. Let it sit for a minute,
then serve immediately and enjoy!